        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 1:56PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 155 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles north of Fort Quitman. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Quitman.

This includes Interstate 10 in Texas between mile markers 88 and 97.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
